The paper proposes a system for Mathematical Information Retrieval, which involves searching for mathematical information using individual formulae or a combination of keywords and formulae. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of similarity metrics and scalability, which are relevant to topics in Deep Learning (cs.DL), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computer Vision (cs.CV).
